The Tampa Bay Lightning, the Stanley Cup Champions, were welcomed to the White House by President Joe Biden. The President praised the team for their back-to-back victories and their contributions to the community. He also mentioned the success of Tampa Bay sports teams, including the Buccaneers and the Rays. The team's owner, Jeff Vinik, expressed gratitude for the invitation and shared his excitement for the upcoming playoffs. Alternate Captain Ryan McDonagh thanked the President for the honor and spoke about the team's historic run. The President was presented with a Lightning jersey and hockey stick.